PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the left peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the middle peg and the left peg are empty again.
The left peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the left peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the middle peg and the left peg are empty again.
The left peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg)

  (:predicates
    ;; disk-on-disk and disk-on-peg represent the direct "on" relation
    (on-disk ?d - disk ?p - disk)
    (on-peg  ?d - disk ?p - peg)

    ;; clear flags for disks and pegs: true when there is no disk immediately on top
    (clear-disk ?d - disk)
    (clear-peg  ?p - peg)

    ;; static size ordering: (smaller X Y) means disk X is strictly smaller than disk Y
    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a top disk from one disk onto another (disk->disk). Requires size ordering.
  (:action move-disk-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on-disk ?d ?from)
      (clear-disk ?d)
      (clear-disk ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))
      (on-disk ?d ?to)
      ;; after removing ?d, its former support becomes clear
      (clear-disk ?from)
      ;; after placing ?d onto ?to, ?to is no longer clear
      (not (clear-disk ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk from one disk onto a peg (disk->peg).
  (:action move-disk-from-disk-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on-disk ?d ?from)
      (clear-disk ?d)
      (clear-peg ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))
      (on-peg ?d ?to)
      (clear-disk ?from)
      (not (clear-peg ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk from a peg onto another disk (peg->disk). Requires size ordering.
  (:action move-disk-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on-peg ?d ?from)
      (clear-disk ?d)
      (clear-disk ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))
      (on-disk ?d ?to)
      (clear-peg ?from)
      (not (clear-disk ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk from a peg onto another peg (peg->peg).
  (:action move-disk-from-peg-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on-peg ?d ?from)
      (clear-disk ?d)
      (clear-peg ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))
      (on-peg ?d ?to)
      (clear-peg ?from)
      (not (clear-peg ?to))
    )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-7)
  (:domain hanoi)

  (:objects
    A B C D E F G - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial stack on peg middle (G is bottom, then F, E, D, C, B, A on top)
    (on-disk A B)
    (on-disk B C)
    (on-disk C D)
    (on-disk D E)
    (on-disk E F)
    (on-disk F G)
    (on-peg  G middle)

    ;; clear statuses: only top-most disk A is clear; pegs left/right start clear, middle not
    (clear-disk A)
    ;; B..G are not listed as clear initially (they are covered) -- absence implies not clear
    (clear-peg left)
    (clear-peg right)
    ;; middle has G on it, so not clear

    ;; full explicit size ordering (static facts). A is smallest, G is largest.
    ;; all ordered pairs (X,Y) with X smaller than Y
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)
    (smaller F G)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; goal: the entire tower moved to peg right in the same order (G bottom ... A top)
    (on-disk A B)
    (on-disk B C)
    (on-disk C D)
    (on-disk D E)
    (on-disk E F)
    (on-disk F G)
    (on-peg  G right)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg)

  (:predicates
    ;; disk-on-disk and disk-on-peg represent the direct "on" relation
    (on-disk ?d - disk ?p - disk)
    (on-peg  ?d - disk ?p - peg)

    ;; clear flags for disks and pegs: true when there is no disk immediately on top
    (clear-disk ?d - disk)
    (clear-peg  ?p - peg)

    ;; static size ordering: (smaller X Y) means disk X is strictly smaller than disk Y
    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a top disk from one disk onto another (disk->disk). Requires size ordering.
  (:action move-disk-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on-disk ?d ?from)
      (clear-disk ?d)
      (clear-disk ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))
      (on-disk ?d ?to)
      ;; after removing ?d, its former support becomes clear
      (clear-disk ?from)
      ;; after placing ?d onto ?to, ?to is no longer clear
      (not (clear-disk ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk from one disk onto a peg (disk->peg).
  (:action move-disk-from-disk-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on-disk ?d ?from)
      (clear-disk ?d)
      (clear-peg ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))
      (on-peg ?d ?to)
      (clear-disk ?from)
      (not (clear-peg ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk from a peg onto another disk (peg->disk). Requires size ordering.
  (:action move-disk-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on-peg ?d ?from)
      (clear-disk ?d)
      (clear-disk ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))
      (on-disk ?d ?to)
      (clear-peg ?from)
      (not (clear-disk ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk from a peg onto another peg (peg->peg).
  (:action move-disk-from-peg-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on-peg ?d ?from)
      (clear-disk ?d)
      (clear-peg ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))
      (on-peg ?d ?to)
      (clear-peg ?from)
      (not (clear-peg ?to))
    )
  )
)

PROBLEM

(define (problem hanoi-7)
  (:domain hanoi)

  (:objects
    A B C D E F G - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial stack on peg middle (G is bottom, then F, E, D, C, B, A on top)
    (on-disk A B)
    (on-disk B C)
    (on-disk C D)
    (on-disk D E)
    (on-disk E F)
    (on-disk F G)
    (on-peg  G middle)

    ;; clear statuses: only top-most disk A is clear; pegs left/right start clear, middle not
    (clear-disk A)
    ;; B..G are not listed as clear initially (they are covered) -- absence implies not clear
    (clear-peg left)
    (clear-peg right)
    ;; middle has G on it, so not clear

    ;; full explicit size ordering (static facts). A is smallest, G is largest.
    ;; all ordered pairs (X,Y) with X smaller than Y
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)
    (smaller F G)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; goal: the entire tower moved to peg right in the same order (G bottom ... A top)
    (on-disk A B)
    (on-disk B C)
    (on-disk C D)
    (on-disk D E)
    (on-disk E F)
    (on-disk F G)
    (on-peg  G right)
  ))
)

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; direct support relations\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?p - disk)\n    (on-peg  ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; clear flags for disks and pegs: true when there is no disk immediately on top\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)\n    (clear-peg  ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; static size ordering: (smaller X Y) means disk X is strictly smaller than disk Y\n    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)\n\n    ;; discrete stage control to enforce strict ordering of moves\n    (current ?s - stage)\n    (succ ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from one disk onto another disk (disk->disk).     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk placement: directly on another disk or directly on a peg\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?p - disk)\n    (on-peg  ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; top-of relations: a disk is clear if nothing is on it; a peg is clear (empty) if no disk is directly on it\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)\n    (clear-peg  ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; size ordering: smaller x y means x is strictly smaller than y\n    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)\n\n    ;; explicit discrete stage/time progression\n    (current ?s - stage)\n    (succ ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a disk to another disk (both disks are on some pegs; target disk must be top)\n  (:action move-disk-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - disk ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)     ;; ?d is directly on ?from\n      (clear-disk ?d)        ;; ?d is top (nothing on ?d)\n      (clear-disk ?to)       ;; ?to is top (we will place ?d onto ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)       ;; size constraint: cannot place larger on smaller\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n      ;; after removing ?d from ?from, ?from becomes clear (nothing on it)\n      (clear-disk ?from)\n      ;; after placing ?d onto ?to, ?to is no longer clear\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a disk to an empty peg\n  (:action move-disk-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)       ;; target peg must be empty\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      ;; after removing ?d from ?from, ?from becomes clear\n      (clear-disk ?from)\n      ;; target peg now has a disk on it and is not clear\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from an empty peg (top disk on a peg) to a disk (target must be top and larger)\n  (:action move-disk-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-disk ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n      ;; the source peg becomes empty after removing its top disk\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n      ;; target disk no longer clear\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a peg to an empty peg\n  (:action move-disk-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      ;; source peg becomes empty\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n      ;; target peg is no longer empty\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi-7-staged)\n  (:domain hanoi)\n\n  (:objects\n    A B C D E F G - disk\n    left middle right - peg\n    ;; stages: one initial plus one per move; 7 disks require 2^7 - 1 = 127 moves, so stages s0..s127\n    s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15 s16 s17 s18 s19\n    s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31 s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39\n    s40 s41 s42 s43 s44 s45 s46 s47 s48 s49 s50 s51 s52 s53 s54 s55 s56 s57 s58 s59\n    s60 s61 s62 s63 s64 s65 s66 s67 s68 s69 s70 s71 s72 s73 s74 s75 s76 s77 s78 s79\n    s80 s81 s82 s83     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk placement: directly on another disk or directly on a peg\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?p - disk)\n    (on-peg  ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; top-of relations: a disk is clear if nothing is directly on it; a peg is clear if nothing is directly on it\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)\n    (clear-peg  ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; size ordering: smaller x y means x is strictly smaller than y\n    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)\n\n    ;; explicit discrete stage/time progression\n    (current ?s - stage)\n    (succ ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a disk to another disk (both are disks; target must be top)\n  (:action move-disk-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - disk ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)     ;; ?d is directly on ?from\n      (clear-disk ?d)        ;; ?d is top (nothing on ?d)\n      (clear-disk ?to)       ;; ?to is top (we will place ?d onto ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)       ;; size constraint: cannot place larger on smaller\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; relocate ?d\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n      ;; moved disk remains top (no disk on it)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      ;; source disk becomes clear (nothing on it) after removal\n      (clear-disk ?from)\n      ;; target disk is no longer clear\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a disk to an empty peg\n  (:action move-disk-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)       ;; target peg must be empty\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      ;; moved disk remains clear\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      ;; after removing ?d from ?from, ?from becomes clear\n      (clear-disk ?from)\n      ;; target peg now has a disk on it and is not clear\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a peg to a disk (target must be top and larger)\n  (:action move-disk-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-disk ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n      ;; moved disk remains clear\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      ;; the source peg becomes empty after removing its top disk\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n      ;; target disk no longer clear\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a peg to an empty peg\n  (:action move-disk-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      ;; moved disk remains clear\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      ;; source peg becomes empty\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n      ;; target peg is no longer empty\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk d is directly on top of disk p\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?p - disk)\n    ;; disk d is directly on top of peg p\n    (on-peg  ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; no disk is on top of this disk\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)\n    ;; no disk is on top of this peg\n    (clear-peg  ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; size ordering: (smaller x y) means x is strictly smaller than y\n    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)\n\n    ;; discrete-time staging\n    (current ?s - stage)\n    (succ ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that sits on a disk onto another disk (both disks must be clear where appropriate)\n  (:action move-disk-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - disk ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)       ;; ?d must be top of its support\n      (clear-disk ?to)      ;; destination disk must have nothing on top\n      (smaller ?d ?to)      ;; size constraint: cannot place larger on smaller\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; remove old support\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      ;; place on new support\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; after moving, ?from becomes clear (nothing on top)\n      (clear-disk ?from)\n      ;; destination is no longer clear\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n\n      ;; moving disk remains clear (has nothing on top)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that sits on a disk onto an (empty) peg\n  (:action move-disk-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)       ;; peg must be clear at top\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; after removing ?d, ?from becomes clear\n      (clear-disk ?from)\n\n      ;; destination peg no longer clear\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains clear\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a peg onto a disk\n  (:action move-disk-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-disk ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes clear after removal\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n      ;; destination disk no longer clear\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains clear\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk d is directly on top of disk p\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?p - disk)\n    ;; disk d is directly on top of peg p\n    (on-peg  ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; no disk is on top of this disk\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)\n    ;; no disk is on top of this peg\n    (clear-peg  ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; size ordering: (smaller x y) means x is strictly smaller than y\n    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)\n\n    ;; discrete-time staging\n    (current ?s - stage)\n    (succ ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that sits on a disk onto another disk (both disks must be clear where appropriate)\n  (:action move-disk-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - disk ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)       ;; ?d must be top of its support\n      (clear-disk ?to)      ;; destination disk must have nothing on top\n      (smaller ?d ?to)      ;; size constraint: cannot place larger on smaller\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))   ;; source and destination disks must be distinct\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; remove old support\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      ;; place on new support\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; after moving, ?from becomes clear (nothing on top)\n      (clear-disk ?from)\n      ;; destination is no longer clear\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains clear (has nothing on top)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that sits on a disk onto an (empty) peg\n  (:action move-disk-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)       ;; peg must be clear at top\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; after removing ?d, ?from becomes clear\n      (clear-disk ?from)\n\n      ;; destination peg no longer clear\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains clear\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a peg onto a disk\n  (:action move-disk-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-disk ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes clear after removal\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n      ;; destination disk no longer clear\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains clear\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a peg onto another peg\n  (:action move-disk-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))   ;; source and destination pegs must be distinct\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes clear\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n      ;; destination peg no longer clear\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains clear\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk d is directly on top of disk p\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?p - disk)\n    ;; disk d is directly on top of peg p\n    (on-peg  ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; no disk is on top of this disk (i.e., disk is the top of its stack)\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)\n    ;; no disk is on top of this peg (i.e., peg is empty)\n    (clear-peg  ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; size ordering: (smaller x y) means x is strictly smaller than y\n    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)\n\n    ;; discrete-time staging\n    (current ?s - stage)\n    (succ ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that sits on a disk onto another disk\n  (:action move-disk-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - disk ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)       ;; ?d must be the top disk of its support\n      (clear-disk ?to)      ;; destination disk must be top (nothing on it)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)      ;; cannot place larger on smaller\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; update support\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source disk becomes top (clear)\n      (clear-disk ?from)\n      ;; destination disk now has something on top (no longer clear)\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk is top on its new support\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that sits on a disk onto an empty peg\n  (:action move-disk-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)       ;; peg must be empty at top (i.e., empty)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; after removing ?d, ?from becomes clear\n      (clear-disk ?from)\n\n      ;; destination peg is no longer clear (now contains a disk)\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains clear (on top)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a peg onto a disk\n  (:action move-disk-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-disk ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes empty (clear)\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n      ;; destination disk is no longer clear\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains clear\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a peg onto another empty peg\n  (:action move-disk-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?ns - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?ns)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source peg becomes clear\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n      ;; destination peg no longer clear\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains clear\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?ns)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi-7-staged)\n  (:domain hanoi)\n\n  (:objects\n    a b c d e f g - disk\n    left middle right - peg\n\n    ;; stages: indexed from s0 (initial) to s127 PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the left peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the right peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the left peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the right peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi7)
  (:requirements :strips :typing)
  (:types disk peg)

  (:predicates
    ; immediate-support predicates
    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)     ; disk is directly on peg
    (on-disk ?d - disk ?s - disk)   ; disk is directly on another disk

    ; top/clear predicates
    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)        ; disk is the top disk on peg
    (clear-peg ?p - peg)            ; peg has no disks
    (clear-disk ?d - disk)          ; no disk is on this disk (it is clear / top)

    ; static size ordering
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto a non-empty peg (onto its top disk)
  (:action move-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk ?top - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on-disk ?d ?below)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (top ?top ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?top)
    )
    :effect (and
      ; remove moved-disk from its current immediate support
      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))
      (not (top ?d ?from))

      ; update the from-peg: the disk that was below becomes the top and becomes clear
      (top ?below ?from)
      (clear-disk ?below)

      ; update the to-peg: previous top is no longer top and no longer clear
      (not (top ?top ?to))
      (not (clear-disk ?top))

      ; moved disk becomes directly on the previous top of destination and becomes the new top
      (on-disk ?d ?top)
      (top ?d ?to)
    )
  )

  ; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto an empty peg
  (:action move-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on-disk ?d ?below)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (clear-peg ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      ; remove moved-disk from its current immediate support
      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))
      (not (top ?d ?from))

      ; update the from-peg: the disk that was below becomes the top and becomes clear
      (top ?below ?from)
      (clear-disk ?below)

      ; update the to-peg: it becomes non-empty and receives the moved disk directly on the peg
      (not (clear-peg ?to))
      (on-peg ?d ?to)
      (top ?d ?to)
    )
  )

  ; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto a non-empty peg (onto its top disk)
  (:action move-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?top - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on-peg ?d ?from)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (top ?top ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?top)
    )
    :effect (and
      ; remove moved-disk from its current peg support
      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))
      (not (top ?d ?from))

      ; from-peg becomes empty
      (clear-peg ?from)

      ; destination: previous top is no longer top and no longer clear
      (not (top ?top ?to))
      (not (clear-disk ?top))

      ; moved disk becomes directly on the previous top and the new top
      (on-disk ?d ?top)
      (top ?d ?to)
    )
  )

  ; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto an empty peg
  (:action move-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on-peg ?d ?from)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (clear-peg ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      ; remove moved-disk from its current peg support
      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))
      (not (top ?d ?from))

      ; from-peg becomes empty
      (clear-peg ?from)

      ; destination: peg becomes non-empty with moved disk on it
      (not (clear-peg ?to))
      (on-peg ?d ?to)
      (top ?d ?to)
    )
  )
)
</domain>
<problem>
(define (problem hanoi7-problem)
  (:domain hanoi7)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )

  (:init
    ; initial immediate-support relations (top-to-bottom on right peg: A,B,C,D,E,F,G)
    (on-disk A B)
    (on-disk B C)
    (on-disk C D)
    (on-disk D E)
    (on-disk E F)
    (on-disk F G)
    (on-peg G right)

    ; top/clear status initial
    (top A right)
    (clear-disk A)
    (clear-peg left)
    (clear-peg middle)
    ; right peg is not clear (no explicit fact)

    ; static size ordering (A < B < C < D < E < F < G)
    ; A smaller than ...
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)
    ; B smaller than ...
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)
    ; C smaller than ...
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)
    ; D smaller than ...
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)
    ; E smaller than ...
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)
    ; F smaller than ...
    (smaller F G)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ; final ordered stack on left: top A, then B, C, D, E, F, G bottom
    (on-disk A B)
    (on-disk B C)
    (on-disk C D)
    (on-disk D E)
    (on-disk E F)
    (on-disk F G)
    (on-peg G left)
    (top A left)
    (clear-disk A)

    ; other pegs must be empty
    (clear-peg middle)
    (clear-peg right)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================

(define (domain hanoi7)
  (:requirements :strips :typing)
  (:types disk peg)

  (:predicates
    ; immediate-support predicates
    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)     ; disk is directly on peg
    (on-disk ?d - disk ?s - disk)   ; disk is directly on another disk

    ; top/clear predicates
    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)        ; disk is the top disk on peg
    (clear-peg ?p - peg)            ; peg has no disks
    (clear-disk ?d - disk)          ; no disk is on this disk (it is clear / top)

    ; static size ordering
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto a non-empty peg (onto its top disk)
  (:action move-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk ?top - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on-disk ?d ?below)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (top ?top ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?top)
    )
    :effect (and
      ; remove moved-disk from its current immediate support
      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))
      (not (top ?d ?from))

      ; update the from-peg: the disk that was below becomes the top and becomes clear
      (top ?below ?from)
      (clear-disk ?below)

      ; update the to-peg: previous top is no longer top and no longer clear
      (not (top ?top ?to))
      (not (clear-disk ?top))

      ; moved disk becomes directly on the previous top of destination and becomes the new top
      (on-disk ?d ?top)
      (top ?d ?to)
    )
  )

  ; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto an empty peg
  (:action move-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on-disk ?d ?below)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (clear-peg ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      ; remove moved-disk from its current immediate support
      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))
      (not (top ?d ?from))

      ; update the from-peg: the disk that was below becomes the top and becomes clear
      (top ?below ?from)
      (clear-disk ?below)

      ; update the to-peg: it becomes non-empty and receives the moved disk directly on the peg
      (not (clear-peg ?to))
      (on-peg ?d ?to)
      (top ?d ?to)
    )
  )

  ; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto a non-empty peg (onto its top disk)
  (:action move-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?top - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on-peg ?d ?from)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (top ?top ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?top)
    )
    :effect (and
      ; remove moved-disk from its current peg support
      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))
      (not (top ?d ?from))

      ; from-peg becomes empty
      (clear-peg ?from)

      ; destination: previous top is no longer top and no longer clear
      (not (top ?top ?to))
      (not (clear-disk ?top))

      ; moved disk becomes directly on the previous top and the new top
      (on-disk ?d ?top)
      (top ?d ?to)
    )
  )

  ; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto an empty peg
  (:action move-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on-peg ?d ?from)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (clear-peg ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      ; remove moved-disk from its current peg support
      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))
      (not (top ?d ?from))

      ; from-peg becomes empty
      (clear-peg ?from)

      ; destination: peg becomes non-empty with moved disk on it
      (not (clear-peg ?to))
      (on-peg ?d ?to)
      (top ?d ?to)
    )
  )

(define (problem hanoi7-problem)
  (:domain hanoi7)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )

  (:init
    ; initial immediate-support relations (top-to-bottom on right peg: A,B,C,D,E,F,G)

    (on-disk C D)
    (on-disk D E)

    (clear-disk A)
    (clear-peg left)
    (clear-peg middle)

    ; B smaller than ...

    ; E smaller than ...

    ; F smaller than ...

  )

    ; final ordered stack on left: top A, then B, C, D, E, F, G bottom
    (on-disk A B)
    (on-disk B C)
    (on-disk C D)
    (on-disk D E)
    (on-disk E F)
    (on-disk F G)
    (on-peg G left)
    (top A left)
    (clear-disk A)

    ; other pegs must be empty
    (clear-peg middle)
    (clear-peg right)
  ))

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing)\n  (:types disk peg)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ; immediate-support predicates\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)     ; disk is directly on peg\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?s - disk)   ; disk is directly on another disk\n\n    ; top/clear predicates\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)        ; disk is the top disk on peg\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)            ; peg has no disks\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)          ; no disk is on this disk (it is clear / top)\n\n    ; static size ordering\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto a non-empty peg (onto its top disk)\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk ?top - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (top ?top ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?top)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; remove moved-disk from its current immediate support\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n\n      ; update the from-peg: the disk that was below becomes the top and becomes clear\n      (top ?below ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?below)\n\n      ; update the to-peg: previous top is no longer top and no longer clear\n      (not (top ?top ?to))\n      (not (clear-disk ?top))\n\n      ; moved disk becomes directly on the previous top of destination and becomes the new top\n      (on-disk ?d ?top)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto an empty peg\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; remove moved-disk from its current immediate support\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n\n      ; update the from-peg: the disk that was below becomes the top and becomes clear\n      (top ?below ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?below)\n\n      ; update the to-peg: it becomes non-empty and receives the moved disk directly on the peg\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto a non-empty peg (onto its top disk)\n  (:action move-from-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?top - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (top ?top ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?top)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; remove moved-disk from its current peg support\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n\n      ; from-peg becomes empty\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ; destination: previous top is no longer top and no longer clear\n      (not (top ?top ?to))\n      (not (clear-disk ?top))\n\n      ; moved disk becomes directly on the previous top and the new top\n      (on-disk ?d ?top)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto an empty peg\n  (:action move-from-peg-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; remove moved-disk from its current peg support\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n\n      ; from-peg becomes empty\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ; destination: peg becomes non-empty with moved disk on it\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n    )\n  )\n)",

disk is directly on peg\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?s - disk)   ; disk is directly on another disk\n\n    ; top / clear predicates\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)        ; disk is the top disk on peg\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)            ; peg has no disks\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)          ; no disk is on this disk (it is top)\n\n    ; static size ordering\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n\n    ; discrete stage progression to enforce sequential single-action steps\n    (current ?t - stage)            ; the current stage\n    (succ ?t1 - stage ?t2 - stage)  ; static successor relation between stages\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto a non-empty peg (onto its top disk)\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk ?top - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (top ?top ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?top)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ; remove moved-disk from its current immediate support\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n\n      ; update the from-peg: the disk that was below becomes the top and becomes clear\n      (top ?below ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?below)\n\n      ; update the to-peg: previous top is no longer top and no longer clear\n      (not (top ?top ?to))\n      (not (clear-disk ?top))\n\n      ; moved disk becomes directly on the previous top of destination and becomes the new top\n      (on-disk ?d ?top)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto an empty peg\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ; remove moved-disk from its current immediate support\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n\n      ; update the from-peg: the disk that was below becomes the top and becomes clear\n      (top ?below ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?below)\n\n      ; update the to-peg: it becomes non-empty and receives the moved disk directly on the peg\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto a non-empty peg (onto its top disk)\n  (:action move-from-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?top - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (top ?top ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?top)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)     ; disk is directly on a peg (bottom disk)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?s - disk)   ; disk is directly on another disk\n\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)        ; disk is the top disk on peg\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)            ; peg has no disks\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)          ; no disk is on this disk (it is a top)\n\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk) ; size ordering: d1 < d2\n\n    (current ?t - stage)            ; current discrete stage\n    (succ ?t1 - stage ?t2 - stage)  ; successor relation between stages\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto a non-empty peg (onto its top disk)\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk ?top - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (top ?top ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?top)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ; remove moved-disk from its current immediate support and its top status on its from-peg\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n\n      ; placed disk becomes directly on the previous top of destination and becomes the new top and is clear\n      (on-disk ?d ?top)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto an empty peg\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ; remove moved-disk from its current immediate support and its top status on its from-peg\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n\n      ;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)      ; disk is directly on a peg\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?below - disk); disk is directly on another disk\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)         ; disk is the top disk on peg\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)             ; peg has no disks\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)  ; size ordering: d1 < d2\n    (current ?t - stage)             ; current discrete stage\n    (succ ?t1 - stage ?t2 - stage)   ; successor relation between stages\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto a non-empty peg (onto its top disk)\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk ?top - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (top ?top ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?top)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ; remove moved disk from its current immediate support and its top status on its from-peg\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n\n      ; expose the disk that was below on the from-peg: it becomes the top\n      (top ?below ?from)\n\n      ; update the destination: previous top is no longer top\n      (not (top ?top ?to))\n\n      ; placed disk becomes directly on the previous top of destination and becomes the new top\n      (on-disk ?d ?top)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto an empty peg\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ; from-peg becomes empty\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ; destination: previous top is no longer top\n      (not (top ?top ?to))\n\n      ; moved disk becomes directly on the previous top and the new top\n      (on-disk ?d ?top)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; from-peg becomes empty\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ; destination: peg becomes non-empty with moved disk on it\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)       ; disk is directly on a peg (bottom disk)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?below - disk) ; disk is directly on another disk\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)          ; disk is the top disk on peg\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)              ; peg has no disks\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)   ; size ordering: d1 < d2 (static)\n    (current ?t - stage)              ; current discrete stage\n    (succ ?t1 - stage ?t2 - stage)    ; successor relation between stages\n    (different ?p1 - peg ?p2 - peg)   ; p1 and p2 are different pegs (init enumerated)\n  )\n\n  ;; move top disk that is directly supported by another disk onto a non-empty peg (onto its top disk)\n  (:action move-from-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?below - disk ?top - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (top ?top ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?top)\n      (different ?from ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ; remove moved disk from its current immediate support and its top status on its from-peg\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n\n      ; expose the disk that was below on the from-peg: it becomes the top\n      (top ?below ?from)\n\n      ; update the destination: previous top is no longer top\n      (not (top ?top ?to))\n\n      ; placed disk becomes directly on the previous top of destination and becomes the new top\n      (on-disk ?d ?top)\n      (top ?d ?to)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the left peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the left peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
; PDDL domain for the classical 3-peg Tower of Hanoi with named disks A..G.
; Modeling choices (explained):
; - Types: a supertype 'place' is used so both 'disk' and 'peg' are usable as destinations or sources.
;   disk - place; peg - place. This lets (on ?d ?p) have ?p be either a peg or a disk.
; - Predicates:
;   (on ?d ?p) : disk ?d is directly on place ?p (p can be a peg or another disk).
;   (clear ?p)  : place ?p (peg or disk) currently has no disk on top (i.e. is a top item or empty peg).
;   (smaller ?d1 ?d2) : static size ordering; true iff d1 is strictly smaller than d2.
; - Two action schemas are provided to avoid disjunctive preconditions:
;   move-to-peg: move a top disk onto an empty peg.
;   move-to-disk: move a top disk onto an empty disk that is larger than the moving disk.
; - Preconditions enforce that only the top (clear) disk can be moved and the destination must be clear.
; - Effects maintain the 'on' and 'clear' facts so there is no bookkeeping token or post-hoc penalty action.
; - No equality precondition is used and :requirements are restricted to :strips, :typing, :negative-preconditions
;   to remain compatible with FastDownward per the specification.
; - This encoding prohibits illegal placements (larger on smaller) by construction.
; - No placeholders or soft constraints; all preferences are encoded as hard constraints.

(define (domain hanoi-domain)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types place disk peg)
  ; Note: disk and peg are subtypes of place so they can be used where a place is required.
  ; (disk - place) is the PDDL syntax: declare disk is a subtype of place.
  (:constants) ; empty constants block  objects appear in the problem file

  (:predicates
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)        ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)
    (clear ?p - place)              ; place ?p has no disk on top (i.e., is a top item or an empty peg)
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk) ; static size relation: d1 is strictly smaller than d2
  )

  ; Move a top disk from any place onto an empty peg.
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)       ; only a disk with nothing on top may be moved
                    (clear ?to)      ; destination peg must be empty (no disk on top)
                   )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              (clear ?from)   ; the place we moved from becomes clear
              (not (clear ?to)) ; the destination peg is no longer clear
             )
  )

  ; Move a top disk from any place onto an empty disk that is larger than the moving disk.
  ; The 'smaller' predicate enforces the size constraint; no larger-on-smaller moves are possible.
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (clear ?to)
                    (smaller ?d ?to) ; moving disk must be strictly smaller than destination disk
                   )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              (clear ?from)
              (not (clear ?to))
             )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
; PDDL problem for 3-peg Tower of Hanoi with 7 named disks A..G.
; Initial configuration: all disks stacked on peg1 with G bottom, then F, E, D, C, B, A on top.
; Goal: move the entire stack to peg3 in the same order (G bottom ... A top).
; All natural-language preferences (e.g., avoid illegal placements) are enforced as hard constraints in the domain.

(define (problem hanoi-problem)
  (:domain hanoi-domain)

  (:objects
    ; Disks named A (smallest) .. G (largest)
    A B C D E F G - disk
    peg1 peg2 peg3 - peg
    ; note: peg and disk types are subtypes of place by the domain declaration
  )

  (:init
    ; Initial stack on peg1: bottom G, then F, E, D, C, B, A (A is top)
    (on G peg1)
    (on F G)
    (on E F)
    (on D E)
    (on C D)
    (on B C)
    (on A B)

    ; Clear facts: only the topmost objects are clear initially (peg2 and peg3 are empty and clear).
    (clear A)
    (clear peg2)
    (clear peg3)

    ; All other 'clear' facts are implicitly false until affected by moves (not listed here).

    ; Size ordering: explicit static 'smaller' relation for all pairs (transitively implied but enumerated).
    ; A is smallest, G is largest. We enumerate all strict pairs where first is smaller than second.
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)
    (smaller F G)
  )

  (:goal
    (and
      ; Final stack on peg3: G bottom, then F, E, D, C, B, A on top.
      (on G peg3)
      (on F G)
      (on E F)
      (on D E)
      (on C D)
      (on B C)
      (on A B)

      ; Ensure other pegs are empty at goal (explicit terminal conditions).
      (clear peg1)
      (clear peg2)

      ; Ensure topmost disk remains clear in final state (A is top on peg3).
      (clear A)
    )
  )
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
; PDDL domain for the classical 3-peg Tower of Hanoi with named disks A..G.
; Modeling choices (explained):
; - Types: a supertype 'place' is used so both 'disk' and 'peg' are usable as destinations or sources.
;   disk - place; peg - place. This lets (on ?d ?p) have ?p be either a peg or a disk.
; - Predicates:
;   (on ?d ?p) : disk ?d is directly on place ?p (p can be a peg or another disk).
;   (clear ?p)  : place ?p (peg or disk) currently has no disk on top (i.e. is a top item or empty peg).
;   (smaller ?d1 ?d2) : static size ordering; true iff d1 is strictly smaller than d2.
; - Two action schemas are provided to avoid disjunctive preconditions:
;   move-to-peg: move a top disk onto an empty peg.
;   move-to-disk: move a top disk onto an empty disk that is larger than the moving disk.
; - Preconditions enforce that only the top (clear) disk can be moved and the destination must be clear.
; - Effects maintain the 'on' and 'clear' facts so there is no bookkeeping token or post-hoc penalty action.
; - No equality precondition is used and :requirements are restricted to :strips, :typing, :negative-preconditions
;   to remain compatible with FastDownward per the specification.
; - This encoding prohibits illegal placements (larger on smaller) by construction.
; - No placeholders or soft constraints; all preferences are encoded as hard constraints.

(define (domain hanoi-domain)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types place disk peg)
  ; Note: disk and peg are subtypes of place so they can be used where a place is required.
  ; (disk - place) is the PDDL syntax: declare disk is a subtype of place.
  (:constants) ; empty constants block  objects appear in the problem file

  (:predicates
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)        ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)
    (clear ?p - place)              ; place ?p has no disk on top (i.e., is a top item or an empty peg)
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk) ; static size relation: d1 is strictly smaller than d2
  )

  ; Move a top disk from any place onto an empty peg.
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)       ; only a disk with nothing on top may be moved
                    (clear ?to)      ; destination peg must be empty (no disk on top)
                   )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              (clear ?from)   ; the place we moved from becomes clear
              (not (clear ?to)) ; the destination peg is no longer clear
             )
  )

  ; Move a top disk from any place onto an empty disk that is larger than the moving disk.
  ; The 'smaller' predicate enforces the size constraint; no larger-on-smaller moves are possible.
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (clear ?to)
                    (smaller ?d ?to) ; moving disk must be strictly smaller than destination disk
                   )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              (clear ?from)
              (not (clear ?to))
             )
  )
)

PROBLEM
------------------------------
; PDDL problem for 3-peg Tower of Hanoi with 7 named disks A..G.
; Initial configuration: all disks stacked on peg1 with G bottom, then F, E, D, C, B, A on top.
; Goal: move the entire stack to peg3 in the same order (G bottom ... A top).
; All natural-language preferences (e.g., avoid illegal placements) are enforced as hard constraints in the domain.

(define (problem hanoi-problem)
  (:domain hanoi-domain)

  (:objects
    ; Disks named A (smallest) .. G (largest)
    A B C D E F G - disk
    peg1 peg2 peg3 - peg
    ; note: peg and disk types are subtypes of place by the domain declaration
  )

  (:init
    ; Initial stack on peg1: bottom G, then F, E, D, C, B, A (A is top)
    (on G peg1)
    (on F G)
    (on E F)
    (on D E)
    (on C D)
    (on B C)
    (on A B)

    ; Clear facts: only the topmost objects are clear initially (peg2 and peg3 are empty and clear).
    (clear A)
    (clear peg2)
    (clear peg3)

    ; All other 'clear' facts are implicitly false until affected by moves (not listed here).

    ; Size ordering: explicit static 'smaller' relation for all pairs (transitively implied but enumerated).
    ; A is smallest, G is largest. We enumerate all strict pairs where first is smaller than second.
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)
    (smaller F G)
  )

  (:goal
    (and
      ; Final stack on peg3: G bottom, then F, E, D, C, B, A on top.
      (on G peg3)
      (on F G)
      (on E F)
      (on D E)
      (on C D)
      (on B C)
      (on A B)

      ; Ensure other pegs are empty at goal (explicit terminal conditions).
      (clear peg1)
      (clear peg2)

      ; Ensure topmost disk remains clear in final state (A is top on peg3).
      (clear A)
    )
  )
)

    "pddl_domain": "; PDDL domain for the classical 3-peg Tower of Hanoi with named disks A..G.\n; Modeling choices (explained):\n; - Types: a supertype 'place' is used so both 'disk' and 'peg' are usable as destinations or sources.\n;   disk - place; peg - place. This lets (on ?d ?p) have ?p be either a peg or a disk.\n; - Predicates:\n;   (on ?d ?p) : disk ?d is directly on place ?p (p can be a peg or another disk).\n;   (clear ?p)  : place ?p (peg or disk) currently has no disk on top (i.e. is a top item or empty peg).\n;   (smaller ?d1 ?d2) : static size ordering; true iff d1 is strictly smaller than d2.\n; - Two action schemas are provided to avoid disjunctive preconditions:\n;   move-to-peg: move a top disk onto an empty peg.\n;   move-to-disk: move a top disk onto an empty disk that is larger than the moving disk.\n; - Preconditions enforce that only the top (clear) disk can be moved and the destination must be clear.\n; - Effects maintain the 'on' and 'clear' facts so there is no bookkeeping token or post-hoc penalty action.\n; - No equality precondition is used and :requirements are restricted to :strips, :typing, :negative-preconditions\n;   to remain compatible with FastDownward per the specification.\n; - This encoding prohibits illegal placements (larger on smaller) by construction.\n; - No placeholders or soft constraints; all preferences are encoded as hard constraints.\n\n(define (domain hanoi-domain)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types place disk peg)\n  ; Note: disk and peg are subtypes of place so they can be used where a place is required.\n  ; (disk - place) is the PDDL syntax: declare disk is a subtype of place.\n  (:constants) ; empty constants block \u2014 objects appear in the problem file\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)        ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)              ; place ?p has no disk on top (i.e., is a top item or an empty peg)\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk) ; static size relation: d1 is strictly smaller than d2\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk from any place onto an empty peg.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n                    (on ?d ?from)\n                    (clear ?d)       ; only a disk with nothing on top may be moved\n                    (clear ?to)      ; destination peg must be empty (no disk on top)\n                   )\n    :effect (and\n              (not (on ?d ?from))\n              (on ?d ?to)\n              (clear ?from)   ; the place we moved from becomes clear\n              (not (clear ?to)) ; the destination peg is no longer clear\n             )\n  )\n\n  ; Move a top disk from any place onto an empty disk that is larger than the moving disk.\n  ; The 'smaller' predicate enforces the size constraint; no larger-on-smaller moves are possible.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n                    (on ?d ?from)\n                    (clear ?d)\n                    (clear ?to)\n                    (smaller ?d ?to) ; moving disk must be strictly smaller than destination disk\n                   )\n    :effect (and\n              (not (on ?d ?from))\n              (on ?d ?to)\n              (clear ?from)\n              (not (clear ?to))\n             )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "; PDDL problem for 3-peg Tower of Hanoi with 7 named disks A..G.\n; Initial configuration: all disks stacked on peg1 with G bottom, then F, E, D, C, B, A on top.\n; Goal: move the entire stack to peg3 in the same order (G bottom ... A top).\n; All natural-language preferences (e.g., avoid illegal placements) are enforced as hard constraints in the domain.\n\n(define (problem hanoi-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi-domain)\n\n  (:objects\n    ; Disks named A (smallest) .. G (largest)\n    A B C D E F G - disk\n    peg1 peg2 peg3 - peg\n    ; note: peg and disk types are subtypes of place by the domain declaration\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ; Initial stack on peg1: bottom G, then F, E, D, C, B, A (A is top)\n    (on G peg1)\n    (on F G)\n    (on E F)\n    (on D E)\n    (on C D)\n    (on B C)\n    (on A B)\n\n    ; Clear facts: only the topmost objects are clear initially (peg2 and peg3 are empty and clear).\n    (clear A)\n    (clear peg2)\n    (clear peg3)\n\n    ; All other 'clear' facts are implicitly false until affected by moves (not listed here).\n\n    ; Size ordering: explicit static 'smaller' relation for all pairs (transitively implied but enumerated).\n    ; A is smallest, G is largest. We enumerate all strict pairs where first is smaller than second.\n    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)\n    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)\n    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)\n    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)\n    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)\n    (smaller F G)\n  )\n\n  (:goal\n    (and\n      ; Final stack on peg3: G bottom, then F, E, D, C, B, A on top.\n      (on G peg3)\n      (on F G)\n      (on E F)\n      (on D E)\n      (on C D)\n      (on B C)\n      (on A B)\n\n      ; Ensure other pegs are empty at goal (explicit terminal conditions).\n      (clear peg1)\n      (clear peg2)\n\n      ; Ensure topmost disk remains clear in final state (A is top on peg3).\n      (clear A)\n    )\n  )\n)",

clear ?p : place ?p has no disk on top (applies to pegs and disks)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n    ;; smaller relation is static: disk ?d1 is strictly smaller than disk ?d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n    ;; at-step marks the current discrete stage\n    (at-step ?s - step)\n    ;; next defines the strict successor relation between stages\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from any place onto an empty peg, advancing from one stage to its successor.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n                    (on ?d ?from)\n                    (clear ?d)\n                    (clear ?to)\n                    (at-step ?s)\n                    (next ?s ?s2)\n                   )\n    :effect (and\n              (not (on ?d ?from))\n              (on ?d ?to)\n              ;; the former support becomes clear (it had ?d as its top)\n              (clear ?from)\n              ;; the destination peg now has a disk on top\n              (not (clear ?to))\n              ;; advance the stage marker\n              (not (at-step ?s))\n              (at-step ?s2)\n             )\n  )\n\n  ;; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (place = peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n    ;; place ?p has no disk directly on top (applies to pegs and disks)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n    ;; static strict size order between disks\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n    ;; current discrete stage marker (exactly one at any time)\n    (at-step ?s - step)\n    ;; strict successor relation between stages\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk ?d (no disk above it) from its current support ?from (peg or disk)\n  ;; onto an empty peg ?to, advancing time from step ?s to its successor ?s2.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n                    (on ?d ?from)\n                    (clear ?d)\n                    (clear ?to)\n                    (at-step ?s)\n                    (next ?s ?s2)\n                   )\n    :effect (and\n              ;; allowed only if ?d is strictly smaller than ?to and ?to has no disk on top.\n  ;; Advances the stage marker from ?s to its successor ?s2.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n                    (on ?d ?from)\n                    (clear ?d)\n                    (clear ?to)\n                    (smaller ?d ?to)\n                    (at-step ?s)\n                    (next ?s ?s2)\n                   )\n    :effect (and\n              ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-domain)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  ;;; Types:\n  ;;;  - disk and peg are subtypes of place (so predicates over place accept disks and pegs)\n  ;;;  - step is a separate type used to model discrete ordered stages\n  (:types disk peg - place step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (place = peg or disk)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n    ;; place ?p (peg or disk) has nothing directly on top of it\n    (clear ?p - place)\n    ;; static strict size order between disks\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n    ;; current discrete stage marker (exactly one at any time is enforced by action effects)\n    (at-step ?s - step)\n    ;; strict successor relation between stages (actions may only advance to direct successor)\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk ?d (no disk above it) from its current support ?from (peg or disk)\n  ;; onto an empty peg ?to, advancing time from step ?s to its successor ?s2.\n  ;; Preconditions ensure only the top disk is moved, destination peg is empty, and the stage advances strictly.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n                    (on ?d ?from)\n                    (clear ?d)\n                    (clear ?to)\n                    (at-step ?s)\n                    (next ?s ?s2)\n                   )\n    :effect (and\n              ;;
