Final state (after s127): all 7 disks A..G are stacked on RIGHT with A at the top and G at the bottom, LEFT and MIDDLE are empty, and the plan reached at-step s127 (127 moves total).
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the left peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the left peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain tower-of-hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    ;; disk placed directly on a place (disk or peg)
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ;; top-of-place is empty (true for pegs that have no top disk, and for disks that have no disk on them)
    (clear ?p - place)
    ;; static size ordering: smaller ?x ?y means disk ?x is strictly smaller than disk ?y
    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a single disk onto an empty peg.
  ;; Preconditions enforce single-disk moves, top-disk-only moves, and forbid moving a disk onto the place it already occupies.
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)      ;; disk is currently on ?from
      (clear ?d)         ;; disk is top (no disk on it)
      (clear ?to)        ;; destination peg has empty top
      (not (on ?d ?to))  ;; destination is not the same place the disk already sits on
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)      ;; after removing top disk, the support becomes clear
      (not (clear ?to))  ;; destination is no longer clear after placing the disk
    )
  )

  ;; Move a single disk onto the top of another disk (must be strictly smaller).
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)        ;; disk is currently on ?from
      (clear ?d)           ;; disk is top (no disk on it)
      (clear ?to)          ;; destination disk is top (no disk on it)
      (smaller ?d ?to)     ;; cannot place larger disk on smaller disk
      (not (on ?d ?to))    ;; destination is not the same place the disk already sits on
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)        ;; after removing top disk, the support becomes clear
      (not (clear ?to))    ;; destination disk is no longer clear after placing the disk
    )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-7-pegs-3)
  (:domain tower-of-hanoi)
  (:objects
    d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 d7 - disk
    pegA pegB pegC - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; Size (static) relations: smaller di dj for all i < j
    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6) (smaller d1 d7)
    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6) (smaller d2 d7)
    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6) (smaller d3 d7)
    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6) (smaller d4 d7)
    (smaller d5 d6) (smaller d5 d7)
    (smaller d6 d7)

    ;; Initial stack: all disks on pegA, largest at bottom (d7), then d6 on d7, ..., d1 on d2
    (on d7 pegA)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)

    ;; Top-of-stack / clear facts initially:
    (clear d1)    ;; smallest disk is top of the stack
    (clear pegB)  ;; empty pegs are clear
    (clear pegC)
    ;; Note: pegA is not clear initially (it has disks), and other disks are not clear because they have disks on them.
  )

  ;; Goal: move the entire tower to pegC preserving order: d7 on pegC, d6 on d7, ..., d1 on d2
  (:goal (and
    (on d7 pegC)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain tower-of-hanoi)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    ;; disk placed directly on a place (disk or peg)
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ;; top-of-place is empty (true for pegs that have no top disk, and for disks that have no disk on them)
    (clear ?p - place)
    ;; static size ordering: smaller ?x ?y means disk ?x is strictly smaller than disk ?y
    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a single disk onto an empty peg.
  ;; Preconditions enforce single-disk moves, top-disk-only moves, and forbid moving a disk onto the place it already occupies.
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)      ;; disk is currently on ?from
      (clear ?d)         ;; disk is top (no disk on it)
      (clear ?to)        ;; destination peg has empty top
      (not (on ?d ?to))  ;; destination is not the same place the disk already sits on
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)      ;; after removing top disk, the support becomes clear
      (not (clear ?to))  ;; destination is no longer clear after placing the disk
    )
  )

  ;; Move a single disk onto the top of another disk (must be strictly smaller).
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)        ;; disk is currently on ?from
      (clear ?d)           ;; disk is top (no disk on it)
      (clear ?to)          ;; destination disk is top (no disk on it)
      (smaller ?d ?to)     ;; cannot place larger disk on smaller disk
      (not (on ?d ?to))    ;; destination is not the same place the disk already sits on
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (clear ?from)        ;; after removing top disk, the support becomes clear
      (not (clear ?to))    ;; destination disk is no longer clear after placing the disk
    )
  )
)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi-7-pegs-3)
  (:domain tower-of-hanoi)
  (:objects
    d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 d7 - disk
    pegA pegB pegC - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; Size (static) relations: smaller di dj for all i < j
    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6) (smaller d1 d7)
    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6) (smaller d2 d7)
    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6) (smaller d3 d7)
    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6) (smaller d4 d7)
    (smaller d5 d6) (smaller d5 d7)
    (smaller d6 d7)

    ;; Initial stack: all disks on pegA, largest at bottom (d7), then d6 on d7, ..., d1 on d2
    (on d7 pegA)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)

    ;; Top-of-stack / clear facts initially:
    (clear d1)    ;; smallest disk is top of the stack
    (clear pegB)  ;; empty pegs are clear
    (clear pegC)
    ;; Note: pegA is not clear initially (it has disks), and other disks are not clear because they have disks on them.
  )

  ;; Goal: move the entire tower to pegC preserving order: d7 on pegC, d6 on d7, ..., d1 on d2
  (:goal (and
    (on d7 pegC)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d1 d2)
  ))
)

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain tower-of-hanoi-staged)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)    ; peg has nothing on it\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk); static size ordering: d1 is smaller than d2\n    (current ?s - stage)           ; current stage/timepoint\n    (next ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage) ;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain tower-of-hanoi-staged)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)    ; disk directly on a peg (bottom-most disk of that peg's stack)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?u - disk)  ; disk directly on another disk (immediately above)\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)         ; nothing on top of this disk (it is the top of its stack)\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)           ; peg has nothing on it\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk); static size ordering: d1 is smaller than d2\n    (current ?s - stage)           ; current stage/timepoint\n    (next ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage) ; successor relation between stages\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is the only disk on a peg to an empty peg\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)    ; disk is top (and thus the only disk on that peg)\n      (clear-peg ?to)    ; destination peg empty\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      (clear-peg ?from)       ; source peg becomes empty\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))   ; destination peg no longer empty\n      (clear-disk ?d)         ; moved disk is top of its new peg (idempotent if already true)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is the only disk on a peg onto another top disk (that must be larger)\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)    ; disk is top (and thus the only disk on that peg)\n      (clear-disk ?to)   ; destination disk is top\n      (smaller ?d ?to)   ; moved disk is smaller than destination disk\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n      (clear-peg ?from)       ; source peg becomes empty\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))  ; destination disk no longer top\n      (clear-disk ?d)         ; moved disk becomes top\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on another disk to an empty peg\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)     ; d is top of its stack\n      (clear-peg ?to)     ; destination peg empty\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      (clear-disk ?from)      ; the disk that was under becomes top\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))   ; destination peg no longer empty\n      (clear-disk ?d)         ; moved disk is top of new peg (idempotent)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on another disk onto another top disk (must be larger)\n  (:action move-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - disk ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (on-disk ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)     ; moved disk is top of its stack\n      (clear-disk ?to)    ; destination disk is top\n      (smaller ?d ?to)    ; moved disk smaller than destination\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n      (clear-disk ?from)     ; disk under becomes top\n      (not (clear-disk ?to)) ; destination disk no longer top\n      (clear-disk ?d)        ; moved disk is top at destination (idempotent)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain tower-of-hanoi-staged)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)    ; disk is directly on a peg (bottom-most disk of that peg's stack)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?u - disk)  ; disk is directly on another disk (immediately above)\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)         ; nothing on top of this disk (it is the top of its stack)\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)           ; peg has nothing on it\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk); static size ordering: d1 is smaller than d2\n    (current ?s - stage)           ; current stage/timepoint\n    (next ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage) ; successor relation between stages (contiguous progression)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is the only disk on its peg to an empty peg\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)    ; disk is top (and thus the only disk on that peg)\n      (clear-peg ?to)    ; destination peg empty\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      (clear-peg ?from)       ; source peg becomes empty\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))  ; destination disk no longer top\n      (clear-disk ?d)         ; moved disk becomes top\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that sits on another disk to an empty peg\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (on-disk ?d ?under)    ;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain tower-of-hanoi-staged)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)      ; disk is directly on a peg (immediately supported by the peg)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?u - disk)    ; disk is directly on another disk (immediately above)\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)           ; nothing on top of this disk (it is the top of its stack)\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)             ; peg has nothing on it\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)  ; static size ordering: d1 is smaller than d2\n    (at ?d - disk ?p - peg)          ; disk's current peg (ultimate peg where its stack resides)\n    (current ?s - stage)             ; current stage/timepoint\n    (next ?s1 - stage ?s2 - stage)   ; successor relation between stages (contiguous progression)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is the only disk on its source peg to an empty destination peg\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (at ?d ?from)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ;; source location updates\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ;; destination location updates\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; update disk's peg\n      (not (at ?d ?from))\n      (at ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; moved disk remains top at destination\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is the only disk on its source peg onto another top disk (destination disk must be larger)\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk ?topeg - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-disk ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (at ?to ?topeg)\n      (at ?d ?from)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ;; source updates: disk leaves the peg, peg becomes empty\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (clear-peg ?from)\n\n      ;; destination updates: disk now on top of destination disk\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; update moved disk's peg\n      (not (at ?d ?from))\n      (at ?d ?topeg)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that sits on another disk to an empty destination peg\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?frompeg - peg ?to - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (on-disk ?d ?under)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-peg ?to)\n      (at ?d ?frompeg)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ;; remove from on-disk relation; underlying disk becomes top\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?under))\n      (clear-disk ?under)\n\n      ;; place on destination peg\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear-peg ?to))\n\n      ;; update disk's peg\n      (not (at ?d ?frompeg))\n      (at ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; moved disk is top on destination\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that sits on another disk onto another top disk (destination must be larger)\n  (:action move-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - disk ?frompeg - peg ?topeg - peg ?s - stage ?s2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (on-disk ?d ?under)\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n      (clear-disk ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (at ?d ?frompeg)\n      (at ?to ?topeg)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ;; remove from its previous support; underlying disk becomes top\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?under))\n      (clear-disk ?under)\n\n      ;; put on top of destination disk\n      (on-disk ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear-disk ?to))\n      (clear-disk ?d)\n\n      ;; update disk's peg\n      (not (at ?d ?frompeg))\n      (at ?d ?topeg)\n    )\n  )\n)",

================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the right peg and the middle peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the left peg and the right peg are empty again.
The right peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the right peg and the middle peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the left peg and the right peg are empty again.
The right peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi7)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types place peg disk)
  ;; pegs and disks are kinds of places
  (:types peg disk - place)

  (:predicates
    ;; direct support relation: disk is directly on a place (peg or another disk)
    (above ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ;; ?d is the top-most disk on peg ?p
    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)
    ;; peg is empty (no disks on it)
    (peg-empty ?p - peg)
    ;; static size order: ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a disk (i.e., its immediate support is a disk)
  ;; to an empty peg.
  (:action move_disk_from_disk_to_empty_peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d ?from)
      (above ?d ?below)         ;; d is directly on disk 'below'
      (above ?below ?from)      ;; that disk 'below' is directly on the source peg
      (peg-empty ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; remove old support
      (not (above ?d ?below))
      ;; d is now directly on peg ?to
      (above ?d ?to)

      ;; update top facts: d is no longer top on ?from, becomes top on ?to
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; destination is no longer empty
      (not (peg-empty ?to))

      ;; the disk that was below becomes the new top on source peg
      (top ?below ?from)
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a disk to be placed on top of another top disk.
  (:action move_disk_from_disk_to_disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d ?from)
      (above ?d ?below)         ;; d is directly on disk 'below'
      (above ?below ?from)      ;; that disk 'below' is directly on the source peg
      (top ?t ?to)              ;; destination peg has top disk t
      (smaller ?d ?t)           ;; size constraint: d must be smaller than t
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; update support
      (not (above ?d ?below))
      (above ?d ?t)

      ;; update top facts: d moves from being top on ?from to top on ?to
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; destination's previous top t is no longer top on ?to
      (not (top ?t ?to))

      ;; the disk that was below becomes the new top on source peg
      (top ?below ?from)

      ;; ensure destination peg is marked non-empty (may already be non-empty)
      (not (peg-empty ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on the source peg to an empty peg.
  (:action move_disk_from_peg_to_empty_peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d ?from)
      (above ?d ?from)     ;; d is directly on the source peg
      (peg-empty ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; update support
      (not (above ?d ?from))
      (above ?d ?to)

      ;; update top facts
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; destination no longer empty
      (not (peg-empty ?to))

      ;; source peg becomes empty after removing its only/lowest disk
      (peg-empty ?from)
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on the source peg to a peg whose top is a disk.
  (:action move_disk_from_peg_to_disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d ?from)
      (above ?d ?from)     ;; d is directly on the source peg
      (top ?t ?to)         ;; destination peg has top disk t
      (smaller ?d ?t)      ;; ensure size constraint
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; update support
      (not (above ?d ?from))
      (above ?d ?t)

      ;; update top facts
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; destination's old top t no longer top
      (not (top ?t ?to))

      ;; source peg becomes empty after removing its bottom/top disk
      (peg-empty ?from)

      ;; ensure destination is non-empty (may already be so)
      (not (peg-empty ?to))
    )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi7-problem)
  (:domain hanoi7)
  (:objects
    left middle right - peg
    A B C D E F G - disk
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial immediate-support (top-to-bottom): A on B, B on C, C on D, D on E, E on F, F on G, G on left
    (above A B)
    (above B C)
    (above C D)
    (above D E)
    (above E F)
    (above F G)
    (above G left)

    ;; top-of-peg facts: A is top of left initially
    (top A left)

    ;; middle and right pegs start empty
    (peg-empty middle)
    (peg-empty right)

    ;; size ordering (static): smaller(x,y) iff x is strictly smaller than y
    ;; A is smallest, G largest
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)
    (smaller F G)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; final immediate-support stack on middle peg: A on B, B on C, C on D, D on E, E on F, F on G, G on middle
    (above A B)
    (above B C)
    (above C D)
    (above D E)
    (above E F)
    (above F G)
    (above G middle)

    ;; top-of-peg: A must be the top on middle
    (top A middle)

    ;; left and right must be empty in the final state
    (peg-empty left)
    (peg-empty right)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi7)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types place peg disk)
  ;; pegs and disks are kinds of places
  (:types peg disk - place)

  (:predicates
    ;; direct support relation: disk is directly on a place (peg or another disk)
    (above ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ;; ?d is the top-most disk on peg ?p
    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)
    ;; peg is empty (no disks on it)
    (peg-empty ?p - peg)
    ;; static size order: ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a disk (i.e., its immediate support is a disk)
  ;; to an empty peg.
  (:action move_disk_from_disk_to_empty_peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d ?from)
      (above ?d ?below)         ;; d is directly on disk 'below'
      (above ?below ?from)      ;; that disk 'below' is directly on the source peg
      (peg-empty ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; remove old support
      (not (above ?d ?below))
      ;; d is now directly on peg ?to
      (above ?d ?to)

      ;; update top facts: d is no longer top on ?from, becomes top on ?to
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; destination is no longer empty
      (not (peg-empty ?to))

      ;; the disk that was below becomes the new top on source peg
      (top ?below ?from)
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a disk to be placed on top of another top disk.
  (:action move_disk_from_disk_to_disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d ?from)
      (above ?d ?below)         ;; d is directly on disk 'below'
      (above ?below ?from)      ;; that disk 'below' is directly on the source peg
      (top ?t ?to)              ;; destination peg has top disk t
      (smaller ?d ?t)           ;; size constraint: d must be smaller than t
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; update support
      (not (above ?d ?below))
      (above ?d ?t)

      ;; update top facts: d moves from being top on ?from to top on ?to
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; destination's previous top t is no longer top on ?to
      (not (top ?t ?to))

      ;; the disk that was below becomes the new top on source peg
      (top ?below ?from)

      ;; ensure destination peg is marked non-empty (may already be non-empty)
      (not (peg-empty ?to))
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on the source peg to an empty peg.
  (:action move_disk_from_peg_to_empty_peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d ?from)
      (above ?d ?from)     ;; d is directly on the source peg
      (peg-empty ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; update support
      (not (above ?d ?from))
      (above ?d ?to)

      ;; update top facts
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; destination no longer empty
      (not (peg-empty ?to))

      ;; source peg becomes empty after removing its only/lowest disk
      (peg-empty ?from)
    )
  )

  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on the source peg to a peg whose top is a disk.
  (:action move_disk_from_peg_to_disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (top ?d ?from)
      (above ?d ?from)     ;; d is directly on the source peg
      (top ?t ?to)         ;; destination peg has top disk t
      (smaller ?d ?t)      ;; ensure size constraint
    )
    :effect (and
      ;; update support
      (not (above ?d ?from))
      (above ?d ?t)

      ;; update top facts
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; destination's old top t no longer top
      (not (top ?t ?to))

      ;; source peg becomes empty after removing its bottom/top disk
      (peg-empty ?from)

      ;; ensure destination is non-empty (may already be so)
      (not (peg-empty ?to))
    )
  )
)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi7-problem)
  (:domain hanoi7)
  (:objects
    left middle right - peg
    A B C D E F G - disk
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial immediate-support (top-to-bottom): A on B, B on C, C on D, D on E, E on F, F on G, G on left
    (above A B)
    (above B C)
    (above C D)
    (above D E)
    (above E F)
    (above F G)
    (above G left)

    ;; top-of-peg facts: A is top of left initially
    (top A left)

    ;; middle and right pegs start empty
    (peg-empty middle)
    (peg-empty right)

    ;; size ordering (static): smaller(x,y) iff x is strictly smaller than y
    ;; A is smallest, G largest
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)
    (smaller F G)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; final immediate-support stack on middle peg: A on B, B on C, C on D, D on E, E on F, F on G, G on middle
    (above A B)
    (above B C)
    (above C D)
    (above D E)
    (above E F)
    (above F G)
    (above G middle)

    ;; top-of-peg: A must be the top on middle
    (top A middle)

    ;; left and right must be empty in the final state
    (peg-empty left)
    (peg-empty right)
  ))
)
================================================================================

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types peg disk step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; immediate support relations\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)    ;; disk ?d directly on peg ?p\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?dd - disk) ;; disk ?d directly on disk ?dd\n\n    ;; top-most disk on a peg\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; peg currently empty (no disks)\n    (empty ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; static size order: ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n\n    ;; explicit discrete time / stage objects and progression\n    (current ?s - step)            ;; current stage\n    (succ ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)   ;; successor relation over stages\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is the top disk on a peg to an empty peg.\n  (:action move_peg_to_peg_empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (empty ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance time\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ;; support updates\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; top updates\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (not (empty ?to))\n      (empty ?from)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is the top disk on a peg to a peg whose top is a disk.\n  (:action move_peg_to_disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (top ?t ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance time\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ;; support updates\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; top updates\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (not (top ?t ?to))\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (not (empty ?to))\n      (empty ?from)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is the top disk on another disk to an empty peg.\n  (:action move_disk_to_peg_empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      ;; note: below is the disk immediately supporting d on the same peg\n      ;; (below may itself be on-peg or on-disk)\n      ;; destination must be empty\n      (empty ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance time\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ;; support updates\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; top updates\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; the disk that was below becomes the new top on source peg\n      (top ?below ?from)\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (not (empty ?to))\n      ;; source peg is not empty because below is now top (so do not set empty ?from)\n      ;; no change to empty ?from here\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is the top disk on another disk to be placed on top of another top disk.\n  (:action move_disk_to_disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?s2)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?t ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance time\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n\n      ;; support updates\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; top updates\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (not (top ?t ?to))\n\n      ;; the disk that was below becomes the new top on source peg\n      (top ?below ?from)\n\n      ;; ensure destination peg marked non-empty (if it were empty, it isn't now)\n      (not (empty ?to))\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types peg disk step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; immediate support relations\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)    ;; disk ?d directly on peg ?p\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?dd - disk) ;; disk ?d directly on disk ?dd\n\n    ;; top-most disk on a peg\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; peg currently empty (no disks)\n    (empty ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; static size order: ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n\n    ;; discrete stage control\n    (current ?s - step)\n    (succ ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is the top disk on a peg to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; stage progression\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?snext)\n\n      ;; support updates\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; top updates\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (not (empty ?to))\n      (empty ?from)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is the top disk on a peg to a peg whose top is a disk.\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (top ?t ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; stage progression\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?snext)\n\n      ;; support updates\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; top updates\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (not (top ?t ?to))\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (not (empty ?to))\n      (empty ?from)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is the top disk on another disk to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; stage progression\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?snext)\n\n      ;; support updates\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; top updates\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; the disk that was below becomes the new top on source peg\n      (top ?below ?from)\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (not (empty ?to))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is the top disk on another disk to be placed on top of another top disk.\n  (:action move-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?t ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; stage progression\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?snext)\n\n      ;; support updates\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; top updates\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (not (top ?t ?to))\n\n      ;; the disk that was below becomes the new top on source peg\n      (top ?below ?from)\n\n      ;; ensure destination peg marked non-empty\n      (not (empty ?to))\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi7-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi7)\n  (:objects\n    left middle right - peg\n    A B C D E F G - disk\n    ;; steps s0 .. s127 (128 steps; minimal solution requires 127 moves)\n    s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15\n    s16 s17 s18 s19 s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31\n    s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39 s40 s41 s42 s43     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types peg disk step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)        ; disk directly on a peg\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?d2 - disk)     ; disk directly on another disk\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)           ; disk is the top disk on peg\n    (empty ?p - peg)                   ; peg has no disks\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)    ; d1 is smaller than d2\n    (current ?s - step)                ; current time step\n    (succ ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)       ; successor relation between steps\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg to an empty peg\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?snext)\n\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n\n      (not (empty ?to))\n      (empty ?from)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto another top disk\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (top ?t ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?snext)\n\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (not (top ?t ?to))\n\n      (not (empty ?to))\n      (empty ?from)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on another disk onto an empty peg\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?below ?from)      ; below must be the disk immediately below d on the same peg\n      (empty ?to)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?snext)\n\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; the disk below becomes the new top of the source peg\n      (top ?below ?from)\n\n      (not (empty ?to))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on another disk onto another top disk\n  (:action move-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?to - peg ?s - step ?snext - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current ?s)\n      (succ ?s ?snext)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (top ?below ?from)\n      (top ?t ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?snext)\n\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (not (top ?t ?to))\n\n      ;; the disk below becomes the new top of the source peg\n      (top ?below ?from)\n\n      (not (empty ?to))\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi7-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi7)\n  (:objects\n    left middle right - peg\n    A B C D E F G - disk\n    s0 s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10 s11 s12 s13 s14 s15\n    s16 s17 s18 s19 s20 s21 s22 s23 s24 s25 s26 s27 s28 s29 s30 s31\n    s32 s33 s34 s35 s36 s37 s38 s39 s40 s41 s42 s43 s44 s45 s46 s47\n    s48 s49 s50 s51 s52 s53 s54 s55 s56 s57 s58 s59 s60 s61 s62 s63\n    s64 s65 s66 s67 s68 s69 s70 s71 s72 s73 s74 s75 s76 s77 s78 s79\n    s80 s81 s82 s83 s84 s85 s86 s87 s88 s89 s90 s91 s92 s93 s94 s95\n    s96 s97 s98 s99 s100 s101 s102 s103 s104 s105 s106 s107 s108 s109 s110 s111\n    s112 s113 s114 s115 s116 s117 s118 s119 s120 s121 s122 s123 s124 s125 s126 s127 - step\n  )\n\n  (:init\n    ;; initial stack on left: top A, then B, C, D, E, F, G at bottom\n    (on-disk A B)\n    (on-disk B C)\n    (on-disk C D)\n    (on-disk D E)\n    (on-disk E F)\n    (on-disk F G)\n    (on-peg G left)\n\n    (top A left)\n\n    (empty middle)\n    (empty right)\n\n    ;; size order: A smallest ...     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types peg disk step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)        ; disk directly on a peg (bottom disk or only disk)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?d2 - disk)     ; Final state after step s127: all disks A (top), B, C, D, E, F, G (bottom) are stacked on the middle peg in correct order; left and right pegs are empty; the plan consumes 127 unit steps (s0  s127) as shown.

Notes:
- Each step exactly corresponds to a plan action in the provided PDDL plan (no actions were added or removed).
- Each action is described with its plan timestamp transition (sX  sY) to show the temporal ordering.
- Each justification is the minimal legality check required by the Tower of Hanoi rules: mover must be top of source, and either target is empty or target's top disk is larger than the moving disk.
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the left peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the right peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the left peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the right peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi-7)
  (:requirements :strips :typing)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)          ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)
    (top ?p - place ?d - disk)        ; disk ?d is the topmost disk on place ?p (used for pegs)
    (empty ?p - place)                ; peg ?p is empty (no disks)
    (clear ?d - disk)                 ; no disk on top of ?d (i.e., it is clear)
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)   ; d1 is strictly smaller than d2
  )

  ;; declare the three pegs as constants (names used by the concrete move actions)
  (:constants A B C - peg)

  ;; Move actions: for each ordered peg pair we provide two variants depending on whether
  ;; the moved disk sits directly on the source peg or on another disk, and for each of
  ;; those we provide two variants for destination being empty vs having a top disk.
  ;; These action schemas strictly enforce: only the top disk of the source may move,
  ;; the target must be empty or have a strictly larger top disk, and only the local
  ;; top/clear/top-of-peg predicates are updated for the affected pegs/disks.

  ;; -- Moves A -> B
  (:action move-A-B-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d A) (top A ?d) (empty B))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d A))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (empty B))
      (on ?d B)
      (top B ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (empty A)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-B-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d A) (top A ?d) (top B ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d A))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (top B ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top B ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
      (empty A)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-B-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top A ?d) (empty B))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (empty B))
      (on ?d B)
      (top B ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (top A ?u)
      (clear ?u)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-B-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top A ?d) (top B ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (top B ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top B ?d)
      (top A ?u)
      (clear ?u)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
    )
  )

  ;; -- Moves A -> C
  (:action move-A-C-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d A) (top A ?d) (empty C))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d A))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (empty C))
      (on ?d C)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (empty A)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-C-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d A) (top A ?d) (top C ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d A))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (top C ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
      (empty A)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-C-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top A ?d) (empty C))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (empty C))
      (on ?d C)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (top A ?u)
      (clear ?u)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-C-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top A ?d) (top C ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (top C ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top C ?d)
      (top A ?u)
      (clear ?u)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
    )
  )

  ;; -- Moves B -> A
  (:action move-B-A-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d B) (top B ?d) (empty A))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d B))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (empty A))
      (on ?d A)
      (top A ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (empty B)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-A-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d B) (top B ?d) (top A ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d B))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (top A ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top A ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
      (empty B)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-A-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top B ?d) (empty A))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (empty A))
      (on ?d A)
      (top A ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (top B ?u)
      (clear ?u)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-A-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top B ?d) (top A ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (top A ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top A ?d)
      (top B ?u)
      (clear ?u)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
    )
  )

  ;; -- Moves B -> C
  (:action move-B-C-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d B) (top B ?d) (empty C))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d B))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (empty C))
      (on ?d C)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (empty B)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-C-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d B) (top B ?d) (top C ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d B))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (top C ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
      (empty B)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-C-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top B ?d) (empty C))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (empty C))
      (on ?d C)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (top B ?u)
      (clear ?u)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-C-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top B ?d) (top C ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (top C ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top C ?d)
      (top B ?u)
      (clear ?u)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
    )
  )

  ;; -- Moves C -> A
  (:action move-C-A-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d C) (top C ?d) (empty A))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d C))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (empty A))
      (on ?d A)
      (top A ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (empty C)
    )
  )

  (:action move-C-A-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d C) (top C ?d) (top A ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d C))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (top A ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top A ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
      (empty C)
    )
  )

  (:action move-C-A-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top C ?d) (empty A))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (empty A))
      (on ?d A)
      (top A ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (top C ?u)
      (clear ?u)
    )
  )

  (:action move-C-A-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top C ?d) (top A ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (top A ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top A ?d)
      (top C ?u)
      (clear ?u)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
    )
  )

  ;; -- Moves C -> B
  (:action move-C-B-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d C) (top C ?d) (empty B))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d C))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (empty B))
      (on ?d B)
      (top B ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (empty C)
    )
  )

  (:action move-C-B-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d C) (top C ?d) (top B ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d C))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (top B ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top B ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
      (empty C)
    )
  )

  (:action move-C-B-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top C ?d) (empty B))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (empty B))
      (on ?d B)
      (top B ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (top C ?u)
      (clear ?u)
    )
  )

  (:action move-C-B-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top C ?d) (top B ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (top B ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top B ?d)
      (top C ?u)
      (clear ?u)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
    )
  )

)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-7-problem)
  (:domain hanoi-7)
  (:objects
    d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 d7 - disk
    A B C - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; ordering relations (total strict ordering by size: d1 < d2 < ... < d7)
    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6) (smaller d1 d7)
    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6) (smaller d2 d7)
    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6) (smaller d3 d7)
    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6) (smaller d4 d7)
    (smaller d5 d6) (smaller d5 d7)
    (smaller d6 d7)

    ;; initial stacking: all disks on peg C, ordered bottom d7 ... top d1
    (on d1 d2)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d7 C)

    ;; top/clear/empty facts reflecting the above
    (top C d1)
    (clear d1)
    (empty A)
    (empty B)
    ;; C is not empty (do not assert (empty C))
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; final stacking: all disks on peg A with same internal order (d1 on d2, ..., d6 on d7, d7 on A)
    (on d1 d2)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d7 A)
    ;; middle peg B must be empty in final state
    (empty B)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi-7)
  (:requirements :strips :typing)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)          ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or disk)
    (top ?p - place ?d - disk)        ; disk ?d is the topmost disk on place ?p (used for pegs)
    (empty ?p - place)                ; peg ?p is empty (no disks)
    (clear ?d - disk)                 ; no disk on top of ?d (i.e., it is clear)
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)   ; d1 is strictly smaller than d2
  )

  ;; declare the three pegs as constants (names used by the concrete move actions)
  (:constants A B C - peg)

  ;; Move actions: for each ordered peg pair we provide two variants depending on whether
  ;; the moved disk sits directly on the source peg or on another disk, and for each of
  ;; those we provide two variants for destination being empty vs having a top disk.
  ;; These action schemas strictly enforce: only the top disk of the source may move,
  ;; the target must be empty or have a strictly larger top disk, and only the local
  ;; top/clear/top-of-peg predicates are updated for the affected pegs/disks.

  ;; -- Moves A -> B
  (:action move-A-B-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d A) (top A ?d) (empty B))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d A))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (empty B))
      (on ?d B)
      (top B ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (empty A)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-B-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d A) (top A ?d) (top B ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d A))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (top B ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top B ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
      (empty A)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-B-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top A ?d) (empty B))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (empty B))
      (on ?d B)
      (top B ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (top A ?u)
      (clear ?u)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-B-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top A ?d) (top B ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (top B ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top B ?d)
      (top A ?u)
      (clear ?u)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
    )
  )

  ;; -- Moves A -> C
  (:action move-A-C-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d A) (top A ?d) (empty C))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d A))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (empty C))
      (on ?d C)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (empty A)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-C-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d A) (top A ?d) (top C ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d A))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (top C ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
      (empty A)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-C-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top A ?d) (empty C))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (empty C))
      (on ?d C)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (top A ?u)
      (clear ?u)
    )
  )

  (:action move-A-C-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top A ?d) (top C ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top A ?d))
      (not (top C ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top C ?d)
      (top A ?u)
      (clear ?u)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
    )
  )

  ;; -- Moves B -> A
  (:action move-B-A-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d B) (top B ?d) (empty A))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d B))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (empty A))
      (on ?d A)
      (top A ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (empty B)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-A-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d B) (top B ?d) (top A ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d B))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (top A ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top A ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
      (empty B)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-A-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top B ?d) (empty A))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (empty A))
      (on ?d A)
      (top A ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (top B ?u)
      (clear ?u)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-A-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top B ?d) (top A ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (top A ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top A ?d)
      (top B ?u)
      (clear ?u)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
    )
  )

  ;; -- Moves B -> C
  (:action move-B-C-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d B) (top B ?d) (empty C))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d B))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (empty C))
      (on ?d C)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (empty B)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-C-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d B) (top B ?d) (top C ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d B))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (top C ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
      (empty B)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-C-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top B ?d) (empty C))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (empty C))
      (on ?d C)
      (top C ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (top B ?u)
      (clear ?u)
    )
  )

  (:action move-B-C-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top B ?d) (top C ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top B ?d))
      (not (top C ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top C ?d)
      (top B ?u)
      (clear ?u)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
    )
  )

  ;; -- Moves C -> A
  (:action move-C-A-from-peg-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d C) (top C ?d) (empty A))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d C))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (empty A))
      (on ?d A)
      (top A ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (empty C)
    )
  )

  (:action move-C-A-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d C) (top C ?d) (top A ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d C))

  )

  (:action move-C-A-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)

      (empty C)
    )

  (:action move-C-B-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d C) (top C ?d) (top B ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d C))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (top B ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top B ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
      (empty C)
    )
  )

  (:action move-C-B-from-disk-to-empty
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top C ?d) (empty B))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (empty B))
      (on ?d B)
      (top B ?d)
      (clear ?d)
      (top C ?u)
      (clear ?u)
    )
  )

  (:action move-C-B-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?u - disk ?t - disk)
    :precondition (and (on ?d ?u) (top C ?d) (top B ?t) (smaller ?d ?t))
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?u))
      (not (top C ?d))
      (not (top B ?t))
      (on ?d ?t)
      (top B ?d)
      (top C ?u)
      (clear ?u)
      (clear ?d)
      (not (clear ?t))
    )
  )

)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi-7-problem)
  (:domain hanoi-7)
  (:objects
    d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 d7 - disk
    A B C - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; ordering relations (total strict ordering by size: d1 < d2 < ... < d7)
    (smaller d1 d2) (smaller d1 d3) (smaller d1 d4) (smaller d1 d5) (smaller d1 d6) (smaller d1 d7)
    (smaller d2 d3) (smaller d2 d4) (smaller d2 d5) (smaller d2 d6) (smaller d2 d7)
    (smaller d3 d4) (smaller d3 d5) (smaller d3 d6) (smaller d3 d7)
    (smaller d4 d5) (smaller d4 d6) (smaller d4 d7)
    (smaller d5 d6) (smaller d5 d7)
    (smaller d6 d7)

    ;; initial stacking: all disks on peg C, ordered bottom d7 ... top d1
    (on d1 d2)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d7 C)

    ;; top/clear/empty facts reflecting the above
    (top C d1)
    (clear d1)
    (empty A)
    (empty B)
    ;; C is not empty (do not assert (empty C))
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; final stacking: all disks on peg A with same internal order (d1 on d2, ..., d6 on d7, d7 on A)
    (on d1 d2)
    (on d2 d3)
    (on d3 d4)
    (on d4 d5)
    (on d5 d6)
    (on d6 d7)
    (on d7 A)
    ;; middle peg B must be empty in final state
    (empty B)
  ))
)

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions :adl)\n  (:types disk peg - place)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; base predicates\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)    ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (peg or another disk)\n    (succ ?a - disk ?b - disk)   ; direct successor in size ordering (a smaller than b)\n  )\n\n  ;; derived predicates to encode ordering and top/empty/clear properties without listing many init facts\n  (:derived (clear ?d - disk)\n    (not (exists (?x - disk) (on ?x ?d)))\n  )\n\n  (:derived (top ?p - place ?d - disk)\n    (and (on ?d ?p) (clear ?d))\n  )\n\n  (:derived (empty ?p - place)\n    (not (exists (?x - disk) (on ?x ?p)))\n  )\n\n  ;; transitive closure of succ to obtain the full \"smaller\" relation without enumerating all pairs\n  (:derived (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)\n    (or\n      (succ ?x ?y)\n      (exists (?z - disk) (and (succ ?x ?z) (smaller ?z ?y)))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from one place to an empty destination place\n  (:action move-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - place)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (top ?from ?d)\n      (empty ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from one place onto a larger disk\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - place ?t - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (top ?from ?d)\n      (top ?to ?t)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?t)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi-7-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi-7)\n  (:objects\n    d1 d2 d3 d4 d5 d6 d7 - disk\n    left middle right - peg\n  )\n  (:init\n    ;; size-successor chain (only direct neighbors) \u2014 yields full ordering via the derived transitive rule\n    (succ d1 d2)\n    (succ d2 d3)\n    (succ d3 d4)\n    (succ d4 d5)\n    (succ d5 d6)\n    (succ d6 d7)\n\n    ;; initial stack on the right peg: top d1 on d2 ... d6 on d7, bottom d7 on peg 'right'\n    (on d1 d2)\n    (on d2 d3)\n    (on d3 d4)\n    (on d4 d5)\n    (on d5 d6)\n    (on d6 d7)\n    (on d7 right)\n  )\n\n  (:goal (and\n    ;; full stack moved to left peg with same internal ordering\n    (on d1 d2)\n    (on d2 d3)\n    (on d3 d4)\n    (on d4 d5)\n    (on d5 d6)\n    (on d6 d7)\n    (on d7 left)\n    ;; middle peg must be empty\n    (empty middle)\n  ))\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-7-staged)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; spatial relations\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)    ; ?d is directly on peg ?p (i.e., the bottom disk on that peg)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?b - disk)  ; ?d is directly on top of disk ?b\n\n    ;; support/top/peg occupancy\n    (clear ?d - disk)              ; no disk is on top of disk ?d (i.e., ?d is the top disk on its peg)\n    (empty ?p - peg)               ; peg ?p currently has no disks\n\n    ;; size relation (static)\n    (smaller ?d - disk ?b - disk)  ; ?d is strictly smaller than ?b\n\n    ;; explicit discrete time / stage control\n    (step ?s - step)               ; stage object\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)   ; successor relation over stages (s2 is immediate successor of s1)\n    (current ?s - step)            ; indicates the stage at which actions may be applied\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk that is currently the sole disk on a peg, to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; location updates\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (empty ?from)\n      (not (empty ?to))\n\n      ;; topness: moved disk remains clear (top)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk that is currently on top of another disk, to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; location updates\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (not (empty ?to))\n\n      ;; the disk that was below becomes top\n      (clear ?below)\n\n      ;; moved disk remains clear (top)\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk that is currently the sole disk on a peg, onto a strictly larger top disk.\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?t)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (not (= ?from ?t)) ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-7-staged)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; structural relations\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)    ; ?d is directly on peg ?p (the bottom disk on that peg)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?b - disk)  ; ?d is directly on top of disk ?b\n\n    ;; support/top/peg occupancy\n    (clear ?d - disk)              ; no disk is on top of disk ?d (i.e., ?d is the top disk on its peg)\n    (empty ?p - peg)               ; peg ?p currently has no disks\n\n    ;; static size relation\n    (smaller ?d - disk ?b - disk)  ; ?d is strictly smaller than ?b\n\n    ;; explicit discrete-time / stage control\n    (step ?s - step)\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)   ; successor relation (s2 is immediate successor of s1)\n    (current ?s - step)            ; indicates the stage when actions may be applied\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is the sole disk on its source peg, to an empty destination peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (not (= ?from ?to))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; location updates\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (empty ?from)\n      (not (empty ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk remains top\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk, to an empty destination peg.\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; location updates\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (not (empty ?to))\n\n      ;; the disk that was below becomes top on its peg/stack\n      (clear ?below)\n\n      ;; moved disk is top\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is the sole disk on its source peg, onto a strictly larger top disk.\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?t)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-7-staged)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; location relations\n    (on-peg ?d - disk ?p - peg)    ; ?d is directly on peg ?p (bottom/anchored on peg)\n    (on-disk ?d - disk ?b - disk)  ; ?d is directly on top of disk ?b\n\n    ;; top/peg occupancy\n    (clear ?d - disk)              ; no disk is on top of disk ?d (i.e., ?d is top)\n    (empty ?p - peg)               ; peg ?p currently has no disks\n\n    ;; static size relation\n    (smaller ?d - disk ?b - disk)  ; ?d is strictly smaller than ?b\n\n    ;; explicit discrete-time / stage control\n    (step ?s - step)\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)   ; s2 is successor of s1\n    (current ?s - step)            ; indicates the current stage\n\n    ;; pairwise inequality helpers (no :equality requirement used)\n    (diff-peg ?p1 - peg ?p2 - peg)\n    (diff-disk ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is anchored on a peg to an empty other peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      (diff-peg ?from ?to)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; location updates\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (not (empty ?to))\n      (empty ?from)\n\n      ;; moved disk remains top\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk, to an empty destination peg.\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-disk ?d ?below)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; remove old on-disk relation, place disk as bottom on destination peg\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-peg ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; peg occupancy updates\n      (not (empty ?to))\n\n      ;; the disk that was below becomes top on its stack\n      (clear ?below)\n\n      ;; moved disk is top on new peg\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk anchored on a peg onto a strictly larger top disk.\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?t - disk ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on-peg ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?t)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n      ;; prevent moving onto a disk that is anchored on the same source peg\n      (not (on-peg ?t ?from))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; location updates\n      (not (on-peg ?d ?from))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; source peg may become empty\n      (empty ?from)\n\n      ;; topness updates\n      (not (clear ?t))\n      (clear ?d)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; location updates\n      (not (on-disk ?d ?below))\n      (on-disk ?d ?t)\n\n      ;; the disk that was below becomes top\n      (clear ?below)\n\n      ;; the target disk is no longer top\n      (not (clear ?t))\n\n      ;;
