    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi-7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (onpeg ?d - disk ?p - peg)      ; disk directly on peg\n    (ondisk ?d - disk ?below - disk) ; disk directly on another disk\n    (clear-peg ?p - peg)            ; peg has no disk on it\n    (clear-disk ?d - disk)          ; no disk on top of this disk\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk) ; d1 is smaller than d2\n    (step ?s - step)\n    (current ?s - step)\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; ================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the left peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the right peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the left peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
Domain:
(define (domain hanoi7)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    ;; a disk is on a place (place = disk or peg)
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ;; nothing on top of this place (place can be a disk or a peg)
    (clear ?p - place)
    ;; static size ordering: (smaller d1 d2) means d1 is strictly smaller than d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a single top disk onto an empty peg (peg must be clear)
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      ;; after placing ?d on ?to its target is no longer clear
      (not (clear ?to))
      ;; the source becomes clear (whether it was a peg or disk under ?d)
      (clear ?from)
    )
  )

  ;; Move a single top disk onto another disk (target disk must be clear and larger)
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
    )
  )
)

Problem:
(define (problem hanoi7-problem)
  (:domain hanoi7)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial stack on left peg: top A, then B, then C, D, E, F, bottom G on peg left
    (on A B)
    (on B C)
    (on C D)
    (on D E)
    (on E F)
    (on F G)
    (on G left)

    ;; only the top disk and empty pegs are clear
    (clear A)
    (clear middle)
    (clear right)

    ;; size ordering (A is smallest, G is largest). List all strict pairs d1 < d2.
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)
    (smaller F G)
  )

  ;; Goal: identical ordered stack on right peg; left and middle must be empty.
  (:goal (and
    (on A B)
    (on B C)
    (on C D)
    (on D E)
    (on E F)
    (on F G)
    (on G right)
    ;; top disk is clear and intermediate pegs left and middle are empty
    (clear A)
    (clear left)
    (clear middle)
  ))
)
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi7)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    ;; a disk is on a place (place = disk or peg)
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ;; nothing on top of this place (place can be a disk or a peg)
    (clear ?p - place)
    ;; static size ordering: (smaller d1 d2) means d1 is strictly smaller than d2
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a single top disk onto an empty peg (peg must be clear)
  (:action move-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      ;; after placing ?d on ?to its target is no longer clear
      (not (clear ?to))
      ;; the source becomes clear (whether it was a peg or disk under ?d)
      (clear ?from)
    )
  )

  ;; Move a single top disk onto another disk (target disk must be clear and larger)
  (:action move-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
      (on ?d ?from)
      (clear ?d)
      (clear ?to)
      (smaller ?d ?to)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?from)
    )
  )
)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi7-problem)
  (:domain hanoi7)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial stack on left peg: top A, then B, then C, D, E, F, bottom G on peg left
    (on A B)
    (on B C)
    (on C D)
    (on D E)
    (on E F)
    (on F G)
    (on G left)

    ;; only the top disk and empty pegs are clear
    (clear A)
    (clear middle)
    (clear right)

    ;; size ordering (A is smallest, G is largest). List all strict pairs d1 < d2.
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)
    (smaller F G)
  )

  ;; Goal: identical ordered stack on right peg; left and middle must be empty.
  (:goal (and
    (on A B)
    (on B C)
    (on C D)
    (on D E)
    (on E F)
    (on F G)
    (on G right)
    ;; top disk is clear and intermediate pegs left and middle are empty
    (clear A)
    (clear left)
    (clear middle)
  ))
)
================================================================================

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg step place - object)\n  ;; note: 'place' is a supertype for pegs and disks; using object typing for compatibility\n  (:predicates\n    ;; a disk is directly on a place (place = disk or peg)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n    ;; nothing on top of this place (place can be a disk or a peg)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n    ;; static size ordering: (smaller d1 d2) means d1 is strictly smaller than d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n    ;; current discrete stage\n    (current ?s - step)\n    ;; immediate successor relation between stages (static)\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a single top disk onto an empty peg (peg must be clear), advancing the current step to its successor.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a single top disk onto another larger disk (target disk must be clear and larger), advancing the current step.\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types place - object\n          disk peg - place\n          step - object)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk d is directly on place p (place = disk or peg)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n    ;; place (disk or peg) has nothing on top of it (is top/empty)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n    ;; size ordering: ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n    ;; temporal progression control: current step and successor relation\n    (current ?s - step)\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a place onto an empty peg.\n  (:action move-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)           ;; ?d is top of its stack (may be on disk or peg)\n      (clear ?to)          ;; destination peg is empty (top)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; update on relation\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      ;; destination peg now has something on top\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      ;; source place now has nothing on top (the item under ?d, if any, is now top)\n      (clear ?from)\n      ;; moved disk is top at its new location\n      (clear ?d)\n      ;; advance time step\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a place onto another top disk (destination disk must be larger).\n  (:action move-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - place ?to - disk ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)             ;; ?d is top of its stack\n      (clear ?to)            ;; destination disk is top of its stack\n      (smaller ?d ?to)       ;; size constraint: cannot place larger on smaller\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; update on relation\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      ;; destination disk is no longer clear (has ?d on top)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      ;; source place now has nothing on top (the item under ?d, if any, is now top)\n      (clear ?from)\n      ;; moved disk is top at its new location\n      (clear ?d)\n      ;; advance time step\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi7-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi7)\n  (:objects\n    a b c d e f g - disk\n    left middle right - peg\n    ;; explicit ordered steps: s1 .. s128 (127 moves     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types place - object\n          disk peg - place\n          step - object)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk d is directly on place p (place = disk or peg)\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)\n    ;; place (disk or peg) has nothing on top of it (for pegs = empty; for disks = top disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)\n    ;; size ordering: ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)\n    ;; temporal progression control: current step and successor relation\n    (current ?s - step)\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a peg onto an empty peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      ;; destination peg now not empty\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      ;; source peg becomes empty\n      (clear ?from)\n      ;; advance time step\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a disk onto an empty peg.\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?under)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?under))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      ;; destination peg now not empty\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      ;; disk under ?d becomes top\n      (clear ?under)\n      ;; advance time step\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a peg onto a top disk (destination disk must be larger).\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      ;; destination disk now has something on top\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      ;; source peg becomes empty\n      (clear ?from)\n      ;; advance time step\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a disk onto a top disk (destination disk must be larger).\n  (:action move-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - disk ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?under)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?under))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      ;; destination disk now has something on top\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      ;; disk under ?d becomes top\n      (clear ?under)\n      ;; advance time step\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi7-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi7)\n  (:objects\n    a b c d e f g - disk\n    left middle right - peg\n    ;; explicit ordered steps: s1 .. s128 (127 moves     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg - place step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)     ; disk ?d is directly on place ?p (a disk or a peg)\n    (clear ?p - place)           ; place ?p (disk or peg) has no disk on top (= top)\n    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk) ; size ordering: ?d1 is strictly smaller than ?d2\n    (current ?s - step)          ; current timestep/state\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step) ; temporal succession\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-peg-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is directly on a peg onto a top disk (destination must be larger).\n  (:action move-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?from)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk to an empty peg.\n  (:action move-disk-to-peg\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - peg ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?under)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?under))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?under)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk that is on top of another disk onto a top disk (destination must be larger).\n  (:action move-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?under - disk ?to - disk ?s - step ?s2 - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (on ?d ?under)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?to)\n      (smaller ?d ?to)\n      (current ?s)\n      (next ?s ?s2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (on ?d ?under))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?under)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (not (current ?s))\n      (current ?s2)\n    )\n  )\n)",
    "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi7-problem)\n  (:domain hanoi7)\n  (:objects\n    a b c d e f g - disk\n    left middle right - peg\n    s1 s2 s3 s4 s5 s6 s7 s8 s9 s10\n    s11 s12 s13 s14
